            <abstract id="ref10" label="Abstract">The 
                <emph render="bold">Curriculum Committee records</emph> detail the activities of the academic committee at Eastern Michigan University. Records are primarily composed of meeting minutes and reports that influenced committee decisions. The records are dated approximately 1937 through 1961, with the bulk from 1949 through 1961.</abstract>
        </did>
        <bioghist id="ref12">
            <head>Administrative History</head>
            <p>The Eastern Michigan University 
                <emph render="bold">Curriculum Committee</emph> made decisions regarding academic curriculum for the entire University. Decisions were influenced by faculty, alumni, and current students. Meeting minutes of the Committee detail the committee members as well as other attendees who presented curriculum proposals.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <prefercite id="ref17">
            <head>Preferred Citation note</head>
            <p>Please cite materials from the University Archives in the following manner: Item. Collection Title. Eastern Michigan University Archives.</p>
        </prefercite>
        <accessrestrict id="ref15">
            <head>Conditions Governing Access note</head>
            <p>Researchers are asked to request materials 24 hours prior to visiting the the University Archives.</p>
        </accessrestrict>
        <scopecontent id="ref14">
            <head>Scope and Contents</head>
            <p>The Eastern Michigan University 
                <emph render="bold">Curriculum Committee</emph> made decisions regarding academic curriculum for the entire University. Decisions were influenced by faculty, alumni, and current students. Meeting minutes of the Committee detail the committee members as well as other attendees who presented curriculum proposals.</p>
            <p>The 
                <emph render="bold">Curriculum Committee records</emph> have been divided into two series: 
                <emph render="bold">Meeting Minutes</emph> and 
                <emph render="bold">Analyses</emph>. The Meeting Minutes include meeting agendas, attendance lists, and minutes, as well as any supplemental information, such as proposals that were discussed at each meeting. The Meeting Minute files have been arranged chronologically by academic year. The Analyses series is composed of reports published on behalf on the Committee in order to identify and evaluate curriculum needs.</p>
        </scopecontent>
